  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the chickpeas and reserve ¼ of them for later. Add the rest to a blender along with just under ½ of the chickpea water. Add ½ the garlic, tahini, juice of ½ the lemon, a good pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil and blend until smooth. Taste and add more lemon juice or salt if needed or more water if it’s too thick."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the mushrooms into quarters (eighths if they’re very large) and melt the butter in a pan. Add the mushrooms to the pan with a good pinch of salt and cook on medium-high heat for 5 mins. Then add the cherry tomatoes and the remaining chickpeas and cook for another 5-8 mins until the tomatoes have started to break down and release their juices. Add a splash of water if it starts to dry out – it should be quite saucy. Slice the sun-dried tomatoes and add these too, along with a tbsp or two of the oil from the jar. Add the harissa, season well and remove from the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the garlic spinach, mince the remaining garlic and add it, along with the spinach, to a frying pan with a little olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook on low heat until the spinach has wilted, about 3 mins, stirring often to make sure the garlic doesn’t burn. Turn off the heat and add a splash of vinegar and stir again."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, spoon 3-4 tbsp of hummus into the base of a bowl, ladle in the saucy harissa mushrooms and top with the garlic spinach. Finish with a drizzle of tahini and olive oil and a squeeze of lemon juice. Scoop it up with a warm pitta."
    }
  ],
